{
  "texts": [
    "Each red dot at the top and bottom represents a data point, meaning that we have 42 (participants) × 10 (texts) = 420 data points for human-generated stimuli.",
    "Each raw data point can only represent either a correct answer (1) or an incorrect answer (0).",
    "The raw data points therefore cannot be scatted across the probability scale.",
    "All data points would normally have to be concentrated at single points.",
    "To be able to see the various data points, we have slightly scatted them around their true values."
  ]
}